  Type Safety Benefits

  # Before (string-based, error-prone)
  if "task" in activity.contexts:  # Typo like "taks" silently fails

  # After (type-safe, compile-time verified)
  if EntityType.TASK in activity.contexts:  # MyPy catches typos!

  The DSL now provides compile-time verification of entity types, transforming your clear domain language into enforceable contracts. This is exactly the "lattice and plant" pattern - the linguistic clarity (15-domain architecture)
  becomes the structural foundation (EntityType enum) on which type-safe code grows.

